---
import { Font } from 'astro:assets';
import ThemeInit from '../../components/tiles/ThemeInit.astro';
import ThemeToggle from '../../components/tiles/ThemeToggle.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Tile A — Warm cinematic dark</title>
		<Font cssVariable="--font-archivo" preload />
		<Font cssVariable="--font-mono" />
		<ThemeInit />
	</head>
	<body>
		<header class="site">
			<a class="mark" href="/tiles/"><img src="/logo.svg" alt="tp mark — back to tile index" width="36" height="36" /></a>
			<p class="tile-tag" style="view-transition-name: tile-a">Tile A — Warm cinematic dark</p>
			<ThemeToggle />
		</header>

		<main>
			<section class="hero reveal">
				<p class="eyebrow">Takis Papadopoulos · Senior product designer · Athens</p>
				<h1 class="display">Making complex things&nbsp;clear.</h1>
				<p class="sub">Twenty years through paper, web, VR, design systems and AI. The medium keeps changing; the job hasn't.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal" aria-labelledby="feel-h">
				<h2 id="feel-h">Feel</h2>
				<p class="max-measure">The minhpham/lusion pole: a dark, warm room where type does the talking and the cinematic layer earns its keep. Bold and wide when it speaks, quiet everywhere else. Personality from words and motion — never decoration.</p>
				<p class="chips" role="list">
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">minimal</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">typographic</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">cinematic</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">warm</span>
					<span class="chip" role="listitem">honest</span>
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal" aria-labelledby="type-h">
				<h2 id="type-h">Type</h2>
				<p class="spec-note">Stand-in face: <strong>Archivo</strong> variable (Omnibus-Type, SIL OFL) — weight 100–900, width 62–125%. Display runs wide (125%) and heavy; body runs normal width. One file, two voices.</p>
				<div class="specimen">
					<p class="spec display">Display / clamp(2.75–7.75rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h1">Heading 1 / clamp(2.1–3.5rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h2">Heading 2 / clamp(1.65–2.35rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h3">Heading 3 / clamp(1.3–1.65rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-h4">Heading 4 / clamp(1.08–1.25rem)</p>
					<p class="spec t-body">Body / clamp(1–1.125rem) — measure capped at 65ch, line-height 1.6, real quotes “like so”, en-dashes – and tabular numerals 0123456789 where figures line up.</p>
					<p class="spec t-small">Small / 0.875rem — metadata, dates, captions’ big sibling.</p>
					<p class="spec t-caption">Caption / 0.8125rem — the quietest voice in the room.</p>
					<p class="spec t-mono">Mono / JetBrains Mono VF — code, tokens, the occasional shell prompt.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal" aria-labelledby="colour-h">
				<h2 id="colour-h">Colour</h2>
				<p class="max-measure">Warm charcoal, warm bone, one amber accent. No pure black, no pure white anywhere. Tokens are authored in OKLCH with hex fallbacks and switch themes via <code>light-dark()</code> — system preference by default, manual override in the header. Dark is this tile's home; the hex fallback (older browsers) is the dark set.</p>
				<div class="swatches">
					<div class="swatch sw-bg"><span>--bg</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-raised"><span>--bg-raised</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-text"><span>--text</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-muted"><span>--text-muted</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-accent"><span>--accent</span></div>
					<div class="swatch sw-border"><span>--border</span></div>
				</div>
				<table>
					<caption>Measured contrast (WCAG 2.2) — also the table component sample</caption>
					<thead>
						<tr><th scope="col">Pair</th><th scope="col">Dark theme</th><th scope="col">Light theme</th><th scope="col">Floor</th></tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>text / bg</td><td>15.63:1</td><td>16.00:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
						<tr><td>muted / bg</td><td>6.80:1</td><td>5.72:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
						<tr><td>accent / bg</td><td>8.48:1</td><td>5.43:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
						<tr><td>text / raised</td><td>14.27:1</td><td>15.20:1</td><td>4.5:1</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal" aria-labelledby="space-h">
				<h2 id="space-h">Space &amp; layout</h2>
				<p class="max-measure">One scale, generous by default — the dark room needs air. Corners barely rounded (4px): cinematic, not friendly-app. Depth comes from raised surfaces, not shadows.</p>
				<div class="space-bars">
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-1)"><span>1 · 0.25rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-2)"><span>2 · 0.5rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-3)"><span>3 · 1rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-4)"><span>4 · 1.5rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-5)"><span>5 · 2.5rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-6)"><span>6 · 4rem</span></div>
					<div style="inline-size: var(--space-7)"><span>7 · 6.5rem</span></div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal" aria-labelledby="comp-h">
				<h2 id="comp-h">Components</h2>

				<p class="max-measure t-body">
					I've designed food-delivery flows, VR tours of ancient stadiums, enterprise design systems and a gaming social network. The thesis project lost its domain and the VR startup never found funding — both taught me more than the wins that followed. These days I split my time between product work and <a href="/tiles/">Zeus</a>, the local-AI studio humming under my desk.
				</p>

				<div class="btn-row">
					<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/tiles/">Read the case study</a>
					<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/tiles/">Download CV</a>
					<a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/tiles/">All experiments</a>
				</div>

				<div class="card-row">
					<article class="card">
						<p class="chip">design systems</p>
						<h3 class="t-h3">BETA CAE — one system, three realities</h3>
						<p class="t-small">Five years building a design system that spans desktop, web and VR/AR for an engineering suite — one language across every screen and headset.</p>
						<a href="/tiles/">Read the case study</a>
					</article>
					<article class="card">
						<p class="chip chip-live">live</p>
						<h3 class="t-h3">Zeus — the local AI studio</h3>
						<p class="t-small">Agents, voice, image generation — running on one stubborn GPU in Athens. Self-funded; self-inflicted.</p>
						<a href="/tiles/">See the experiments</a>
					</article>
				</div>

				<aside class="callout">
					<p class="t-small"><strong>Token discipline.</strong> Every visual decision on this page is a custom property. Change it once, it changes everywhere — the same contract the real site keeps in <code>design.md</code>.</p>
				</aside>

				<figure>
					<pre class="code"><code>/* the scroll choreography on this very page — CSS only, no JS */
@supports (animation-timeline: view()) &#123;
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) &#123;
    .reveal &#123;
      animation: rise 1ms linear both;
      animation-timeline: view();
      animation-range: entry 0% entry 55%;
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
					<figcaption class="t-caption">Figure + caption sample. The code block is real — it drives the reveals here.</figcaption>
				</figure>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal" aria-labelledby="motion-h">
				<h2 id="motion-h">Motion</h2>
				<ul class="max-measure">
					<li><code>--motion-quick: 120ms</code> — hovers, presses (try the buttons above).</li>
					<li><code>--motion-base: 240ms</code> — reveals, theme changes.</li>
					<li><strong>Signature:</strong> cross-document View Transition — <a href="/tiles/">go back to the index</a> and watch the tile title morph. Pure CSS, zero JS.</li>
					<li><strong>Choreography:</strong> sections on this page rise as they enter the viewport — CSS scroll-driven animation, no observer, no library.</li>
					<li><strong>Reduced motion:</strong> everything above collapses to plain visibility. The page never needs motion to be read.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal" aria-labelledby="nf-h">
				<h2 id="nf-h">404 sample</h2>
				<div class="frame-404">
					<p class="display nf-code">404</p>
					<p class="t-h3">Nothing here but very good kerning.</p>
					<p class="t-small">Either the link is old or I broke it. My money's on me.</p>
					<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/tiles/">Go home</a>
				</div>
			</section>

			<footer class="colophon">
				<p class="t-caption">Stand-in fonts: Archivo (Omnibus-Type) + JetBrains Mono — both SIL OFL, self-hosted woff2, subsetting allowed. Premium upgrade candidates for this direction: <strong>PP Neue Montreal</strong> (Pangram Pangram — web licence priced per page-view tier per weight, free personal trial) or <strong>Söhne</strong> (Klim — one-off perpetual web licence, ~USD 60/style class, self-host woff2 as provided, no modification). Exact prices at the foundry checkout; subsetting rights checked before any purchase. Buying is a takis decision after the tile pick.</p>
				<p class="t-caption">Theme: system default + manual override. Colours: OKLCH via <code>light-dark()</code>, hex fallback = dark set (this tile's home). Style tile — deleted after Phase 1 pick.</p>
			</footer>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
	:root { color-scheme: light dark; }
	:root[data-theme='light'] { color-scheme: light; }
	:root[data-theme='dark'] { color-scheme: dark; }
	@view-transition { navigation: auto; }

	:root {
		/* ---- Tile A tokens. Hex fallback = dark (home theme); capable browsers get OKLCH light-dark() ---- */
		--bg: #161210;
		--bg: light-dark(oklch(97.2% 0.011 76.6), oklch(18.6% 0.008 48.3));
		--bg-raised: #221b15;
		--bg-raised: light-dark(oklch(94.3% 0.018 78.2), oklch(22.8% 0.016 62.5));
		--text: #f2eae1;
		--text: light-dark(oklch(22% 0.016 62.5), oklch(94.1% 0.015 70.9));
		--text-muted: #a89a8c;
		--text-muted: light-dark(oklch(49.3% 0.025 69.4), oklch(69.4% 0.026 67.4));
		--accent: #e8a04c;
		--accent: light-dark(oklch(50.9% 0.096 67.6), oklch(76.1% 0.131 67.6));
		--accent-contrast: #161210;
		--accent-contrast: light-dark(oklch(97.2% 0.011 76.6), oklch(18.6% 0.008 48.3));
		--border: #3a312a;
		--border: light-dark(oklch(87.2% 0.027 76.8), oklch(32.1% 0.018 60));
		--focus-ring: var(--accent);

		/* type */
		--size-display: clamp(2.75rem, 1.1rem + 8.8vw, 7.75rem);
		--size-h1: clamp(2.1rem, 1.4rem + 2.8vw, 3.5rem);
		--size-h2: clamp(1.65rem, 1.3rem + 1.4vw, 2.35rem);
		--size-h3: clamp(1.3rem, 1.15rem + 0.7vw, 1.65rem);
		--size-h4: clamp(1.08rem, 1rem + 0.35vw, 1.25rem);
		--size-body: clamp(1rem, 0.96rem + 0.2vw, 1.125rem);
		--size-small: 0.875rem;
		--size-caption: 0.8125rem;

		/* space */
		--space-1: 0.25rem; --space-2: 0.5rem; --space-3: 1rem; --space-4: 1.5rem;
		--space-5: 2.5rem; --space-6: 4rem; --space-7: 6.5rem;

		/* motion */
		--motion-quick: 120ms;
		--motion-base: 240ms;
		--ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.7, 0.2, 1);

		--radius: 4px;
	}

	* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; }
	body {
		background: var(--bg);
		color: var(--text);
		font-family: var(--font-archivo), system-ui, sans-serif;
		font-size: var(--size-body);
		line-height: 1.6;
		padding: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem);
		max-width: 68rem;
		margin-inline: auto;
	}
	:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--focus-ring); outline-offset: 3px; border-radius: 2px; }
	a { color: var(--accent); text-underline-offset: 0.2em; transition: opacity var(--motion-quick) var(--ease-out); }
	a:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

	.site { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
	.tile-tag { font-size: var(--size-small); color: var(--text-muted); letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; }
	#theme-toggle {
		font: inherit; font-size: var(--size-caption); cursor: pointer; padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem;
		border-radius: 999px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-raised); color: var(--text);
	}

	main > section { margin-bottom: var(--space-7); }
	h2 { font-size: var(--size-h2); font-weight: 750; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
	.max-measure { max-width: 65ch; }

	.hero { padding-block: var(--space-6); }
	.eyebrow { font-size: var(--size-small); color: var(--text-muted); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
	.display {
		font-size: var(--size-display);
		font-weight: 840;
		font-stretch: 125%;
		line-height: 0.98;
		letter-spacing: -0.025em;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
	}
	.sub { font-size: var(--size-h4); color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 45ch; }

	/* type specimen */
	.spec-note { color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 65ch; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
	.specimen { display: grid; gap: var(--space-3); border-block: 1px solid var(--border); padding-block: var(--space-4); }
	.spec.display { margin: 0; }
	.t-h1 { font-size: var(--size-h1); font-weight: 800; font-stretch: 118%; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.05; }
	.t-h2 { font-size: var(--size-h2); font-weight: 750; letter-spacing: -0.015em; }
	.t-h3 { font-size: var(--size-h3); font-weight: 700; }
	.t-h4 { font-size: var(--size-h4); font-weight: 650; }
	.t-body { font-size: var(--size-body); max-width: 65ch; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
	.t-small { font-size: var(--size-small); color: var(--text-muted); }
	.t-caption { font-size: var(--size-caption); color: var(--text-muted); }
	.t-mono { font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace; font-size: var(--size-small); }

	/* colour */
	.swatches { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(9rem, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-2); margin-block: var(--space-4); }
	.swatch { border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-3); font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace; font-size: var(--size-caption); }
	.sw-bg { background: var(--bg); }
	.sw-raised { background: var(--bg-raised); }
	.sw-text { background: var(--text); color: var(--bg); }
	.sw-muted { background: var(--text-muted); color: var(--bg); }
	.sw-accent { background: var(--accent); color: var(--accent-contrast); }
	.sw-border { background: var(--border); }
	table { border-collapse: collapse; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-size: var(--size-small); }
	caption { text-align: left; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: var(--size-caption); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
	th, td { text-align: left; padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4) var(--space-2) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }

	/* space */
	.space-bars { display: grid; gap: var(--space-2); margin-top: var(--space-4); }
	.space-bars div { background: var(--accent); block-size: 1.1rem; border-radius: 2px; position: relative; min-inline-size: 2px; }
	.space-bars span { position: absolute; inset-inline-start: calc(100% + 0.75rem); top: 50%; translate: 0 -50%; font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace; font-size: var(--size-caption); color: var(--text-muted); white-space: nowrap; }

	/* components */
	.chips { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-2); margin-top: var(--space-3); }
	.chip { display: inline-block; font-size: var(--size-caption); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.2rem 0.7rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
	.chip-live { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); }
	.btn-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-3); margin-block: var(--space-5); }
	.btn { display: inline-block; padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem; border-radius: var(--radius); font-weight: 650; text-decoration: none; transition: translate var(--motion-quick) var(--ease-out), opacity var(--motion-quick) var(--ease-out); }
	.btn:hover { translate: 0 -2px; opacity: 1; }
	.btn:active { translate: 0 0; }
	.btn-primary { background: var(--accent); color: var(--accent-contrast); }
	.btn-secondary { border: 1px solid var(--text); color: var(--text); }
	.btn-ghost { color: var(--accent); }
	.card-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(17rem, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-4); margin-block: var(--space-5); }
	.card { background: var(--bg-raised); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: var(--space-4); display: grid; gap: var(--space-3); align-content: start; justify-items: start; }
	.callout { border-inline-start: 3px solid var(--accent); background: var(--bg-raised); padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4); border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0; max-width: 65ch; margin-block: var(--space-5); }
	.callout .t-small { color: var(--text); }
	figure { margin-block: var(--space-5); }
	.code { background: var(--bg-raised); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: var(--space-4); overflow-x: auto; font-family: var(--font-mono), monospace; font-size: var(--size-small); line-height: 1.55; margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
	.code code { font-family: inherit; }

	/* 404 sample */
	.frame-404 { border: 1px dashed var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4); display: grid; gap: var(--space-3); justify-items: center; text-align: center; }
	.nf-code { font-size: clamp(4rem, 16vw, 11rem); margin: 0; }

	.colophon { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: var(--space-4); display: grid; gap: var(--space-2); }

	/* scroll choreography — CSS only, progressive, reduced-motion off */
	@keyframes rise { from { opacity: 0; translate: 0 1.5rem; } to { opacity: 1; translate: 0 0; } }
	@supports (animation-timeline: view()) {
		@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
			.reveal {
				animation: rise 1ms linear both;
				animation-timeline: view();
				animation-range: entry 0% entry 55%;
			}
		}
	}
	@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
		.btn, a, .tile-card { transition: none; }
	}
</style>
